The finally block in Java is used to execute a block of code after a try-catch block. It is used to release system resources, close connections, and perform other cleanup operations. The finalize method in Java is a special method that is called by the garbage collector to release system resources. The main difference between finally and finalize is that finally is used for manual resource management, while finalize is used for automatic resource management. Here's an example of using the finally block to close a file: 

 try { 
 // code to open and read a file 
 } catch (Exception e) { 
 // code to handle the exception 
 } finally { 
 // code to close the file 
 }

